Kenya’s Central Bank will offer re-opened 20- and 25-year Treasury bonds at this month’s auction, seeking to raise a total of Sh50 billion ($486.38 million), it said on Monday. The bonds, which will be auctioned on March 18, come with a coupon rate of 13.20% and 13.40% for the 20- and 25-year tenors respectively, the bank said in a statement. The bank will rediscount the bonds at 3% above the prevailing market yield or coupon rate, subject to approval by the Nairobi Securities Exchange, it said.